{"title": "Sizeshifter", "content": "A very specific type of superpower. The character has the ability to change their size. Usually, this starts off one way, such as only being able to shrink or grow. Eventually, this starts to seem a little lame (unless the change comes with added Super Strength, or other Required Secondary Powers in order to offset that pesky Square-Cube Law), and they probably end up being able to do both with an upgrade of some sort, or a Hand Wave about training.\n\nIn the case where outfits don't follow suit with the character, most particularly in shrinking, it's likely to cause Shapeshifting Excludes Clothing. Also, don't even try to think about those pesky conservation laws, they don't exist, as far as Sizeshifters are concerned.\n\nCompare Make My Monster Grow, where a character makes a monster grow to great heights, and Shameful Shrinking, where the size change is more metaphorical than real. Supertrope to Hulking Out, where the size shift happens due to anger.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Sizeshifter?from=Main.Sizeshifting", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperMarioBros", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/KillLaKill", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/InuYasha", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Guyver", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MazingerZ", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/GreatMazinger", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/DragonBall", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DragonBall", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DragonBallZ", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DragonBallZLordSlug", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OnePiece", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/LyricalNanoha", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MagicalGirlLyricalNanohaVivid", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MyHeroAcademia", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/AntMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/YoungAvengers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Wasp", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Superman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/XMen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Com